  <description>
    <p>
      (Rclone Shuttle is still experimental. If you prefer a more mature but unmaintained alternative, we recommend Rclone Browser.)
    </p>
    <p>
      Access all your cloud storage providers from one app. Powered by Rclone's superb command line tool, Rclone Shuttle lets you browse your files wherever they are hosted.
    </p>
    <p>Rclone Shuttle can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Upload files via drag and drop</li>
      <li>Rename, move, copy and delete files/folders</li>
      <li>Open remote files locally via double click</li>
      <li>Handle encrypted Rclone configuration files</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Rclone supports a variety of providers and protocols including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Amazon S3</li>
      <li>Dropbox</li>
      <li>FTP</li>
      <li>Google Cloud Storage</li>
      <li>Google Drive</li>
      <li>Google Photos</li>
      <li>OneDrive</li>
      <li>Proton Drive</li>
      <li>SFTP</li>
      <li>SMB (Samba)</li>
      <li>WebDAV (works with Nextcloud)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Full host filesystem access is necessary to enable drag-and-drop until https://github.com/pieterdd/RcloneShuttle/issues/7 is fixed.</p>
  </description>
  
